<subSubSection pageId="385" pageNumber="386" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="385" pageNumber="386">
Subgenus 
<taxonomicName LSID="0D0466FE-3F7D-518D-B4EB-49D24456C7A5" authority="Casey, 1918" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="(Cyclolopha)" order="Coleoptera" pageId="385" pageNumber="386" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Cyclolopha">Cyclolopha Casey, 1918</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="385" pageNumber="386" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="385" pageNumber="386">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Cyclolopha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="385" pageNumber="386" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Cyclolopha</taxonomicName>
Casey, 1918: 144. Type species: 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="385" pageNumber="386" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sphaeroderum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="385" pageNumber="386">Bembidium sphaeroderum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bates, 1882 designated by Erwin (1982b: 483). Etymology. From the Greek 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="385" pageNumber="386">cyclos</emphasis>
(circle) and the generic name 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Lopha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="385" pageNumber="386" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="385" pageNumber="386">Lopha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="385" pageNumber="386">q.v</emphasis>
.], alluding to the sphaerical body shape (&quot;oblong-oval, convex body&quot;) of adults of these 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Lopha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="385" pageNumber="386" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="385" pageNumber="386">Lopha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-like species [feminine].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="385" pageNumber="386" type="diversity">
<paragraph pageId="385" pageNumber="386">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="385" pageNumber="386">Six Neotropical species of which three extend into southwestern North America.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="385" pageNumber="386" type="identification">
<paragraph pageId="385" pageNumber="386">Identification.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="385" pageNumber="386">
Perrault (1982a) revised the species except 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Horn" authorityYear="1895" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="385" pageNumber="386" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jucundum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="385" pageNumber="386">Bembidion jucundum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Horn.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
